Benjamin Michael Utt (born June 13, 1959 in Richmond, California) is a former American football guard who played eight seasons in the National Football League for the Baltimore/Indianapolis Colts. Married to Elizabeth Utt and father to two children: Garrett and Olivia. Garrett currently plays[when?] Division 1 football at Duke University, while Olivia is recruited by colleges for basketball as only a freshman in high school. 
